defs.docs: "Fallible" iterators.

defs.name: FallibleIterator
defs.docs: An `Iterator`-like trait that allows for calculation of items to fail.

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: The type being iterated over.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: The error type.

defs.name: next
defs.docs: Advances the iterator and returns the next value.

defs.name: size_hint
defs.docs: Returns bounds on the remaining length of the iterator.

defs.name: count
defs.docs: Consumes the iterator, returning the number of remaining items.

defs.name: last
defs.docs: Returns the last element of the iterator.

defs.name: nth
defs.value: fn (&mut self, mut n: usize) -> Result<Option<Self::Item>, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Returns the `n`th element of the iterator.

defs.name: step_by
defs.docs: Returns an iterator starting at the same point, but stepping by the given amount at each iteration.

defs.name: chain
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which yields the elements of this iterator followed
 by another.

defs.name: zip
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator that yields pairs of this iterator's and another
 iterator's values.

defs.name: map
defs.value: fn <F, B> (self, f: F) -> Map<Self, F>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which applies a fallible transform to the elements
 of the underlying iterator.

defs.name: for_each
defs.value: fn <F> (self, mut f: F) -> Result<(), Self::Error>
defs.docs: Calls a fallible closure on each element of an iterator.

defs.name: filter
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which uses a predicate to determine which values
 should be yielded. The predicate may fail; such failures are passed to
 the caller.

defs.name: filter_map
defs.value: fn <B, F> (self, f: F) -> FilterMap<Self, F>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which both filters and maps. The closure may fail;
 such failures are passed along to the consumer.

defs.name: enumerate
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which yields the current iteration count as well
 as the value.

defs.name: peekable
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator that can peek at the next element without consuming
 it.

defs.name: skip_while
defs.docs: Returns an iterator that skips elements based on a predicate.

defs.name: take_while
defs.docs: Returns an iterator that yields elements based on a predicate.

defs.name: skip
defs.docs: Returns an iterator which skips the first `n` values of this iterator.

defs.name: take
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator that yields only the first `n` values of this
 iterator.

defs.name: scan
defs.value: fn <St, B, F> (self, initial_state: St, f: F) -> Scan<Self, St, F>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which applies a stateful map to values of this
 iterator.

defs.name: flat_map
defs.value: fn <U, F> (self, f: F) -> FlatMap<Self, U, F>
defs.docs: Returns an iterator which maps this iterator's elements to iterators, yielding those iterators' values.

defs.name: flatten
defs.docs: Returns an iterator which flattens an iterator of iterators, yielding those iterators' values.

defs.name: fuse
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator which yields this iterator's elements and ends after
 the first `Ok(None)`.

defs.name: inspect
defs.docs: Returns an iterator which passes each element to a closure before returning it.

defs.name: by_ref
defs.docs: Borrow an iterator rather than consuming it.

defs.name: collect
defs.docs: Transforms the iterator into a collection.

defs.name: partition
defs.value: fn <B, F> (self, mut f: F) -> Result<(B, B), Self::Error>
defs.docs: Transforms the iterator into two collections, partitioning elements by a closure.

defs.name: fold
defs.value: fn <B, F> (mut self, init: B, f: F) -> Result<B, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Applies a function over the elements of the iterator, producing a single
 final value.

defs.name: try_fold
defs.value: fn <B, E, F> (&mut self, mut init: B, mut f: F) -> Result<B, E>
defs.docs: Applies a function over the elements of the iterator, producing a single final value.

defs.name: all
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Determines if all elements of this iterator match a predicate.

defs.name: any
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Determines if any element of this iterator matches a predicate.

defs.name: find
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<Option<Self::Item>, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Returns the first element of the iterator that matches a predicate.

defs.name: find_map
defs.value: fn <B, F> (&mut self, f: F) -> Result<Option<B>, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Applies a function to the elements of the iterator, returning the first non-`None` result.

defs.name: position
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<Option<usize>, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Returns the position of the first element of this iterator that matches
 a predicate. The predicate may fail; such failures are returned to the
 caller.

defs.name: max
defs.docs: Returns the maximal element of the iterator.

defs.docs:
Returns the element of the iterator which gives the maximum value from
 the function.

defs.name: max_by
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<Option<Self::Item>, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Returns the element that gives the maximum value with respect to the function.

defs.name: min
defs.docs: Returns the minimal element of the iterator.

defs.name: min_by_key
defs.value: fn <B, F> (mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<Option<Self::Item>, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Returns the element of the iterator which gives the minimum value from
 the function.

defs.name: min_by
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self, mut f: F) -> Result<Option<Self::Item>, Self::Error>
defs.docs: Returns the element that gives the minimum value with respect to the function.

defs.name: rev
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator that yields this iterator's items in the opposite
 order.

defs.name: unzip
defs.value: fn <A, B, FromA, FromB> (self) -> Result<(FromA, FromB), Self::Error>
defs.docs: Converts an iterator of pairs into a pair of containers.

defs.name: cloned
defs.docs: Returns an iterator which clones all of its elements.

defs.name: cycle
defs.docs: Returns an iterator which repeas this iterator endlessly.

defs.docs:
Lexicographically compares the elements of this iterator to that of
 another.

defs.name: partial_cmp

defs.docs:
Lexicographically compares the elements of this iterator to that of
 another.

defs.name: eq
defs.value: fn <I> (mut self, other: I) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Determines if the elements of this iterator are equal to those of
 another.

defs.name: ne
defs.value: fn <I> (mut self, other: I) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Determines if the elements of this iterator are not equal to those of
 another.

defs.name: lt
defs.value: fn <I> (mut self, other: I) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Determines if the elements of this iterator are lexicographically less
 than those of another.

defs.name: le
defs.value: fn <I> (mut self, other: I) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Determines if the elements of this iterator are lexicographically less
 than or equal to those of another.

defs.name: gt
defs.value: fn <I> (mut self, other: I) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Determines if the elements of this iterator are lexicographically
 greater than those of another.

defs.name: ge
defs.value: fn <I> (mut self, other: I) -> Result<bool, Self::Error>
defs.docs:
Determines if the elements of this iterator are lexicographically
 greater than or equal to those of another.

defs.docs: The error value of the iterator.

An iterator which applies a fallible transform to the elements of the
 underlying iterator.

An iterator that yields the iteration count as well as the values of the
 underlying iterator.

An iterator which uses a fallible predicate to determine which values of the
 underlying iterator should be yielded.

An iterator which both filters and maps the values of the underlying
 iterator.

 iterator.

An iterator which yields elements of the underlying iterator in reverse
 order.

defs.docs: An iterator which skips initial elements.

An iterator which yields a limited number of elements from the underlying
 iterator.

defs.docs: An iterator which yields elements based on a predicate.

defs.docs: An iterator which cycles another endlessly.

defs.docs:
An iterator that yields pairs of this iterator's and another iterator's
 values.
